an incident involving a vehicle they own, such as in a _t_r_a_f_f_i_c_ _c_o_l_l_i_s_i_o_n.
Coverage typically includes:
    * Property coverage, for damage to or theft of the car
    * Liability coverage, for the legal responsibility to others for bodily
      injury or property damage
    * Medical coverage, for the cost of treating injuries, rehabilitation and
      sometimes lost wages and funeral expenses
Most countries, such as the _U_n_i_t_e_d_ _K_i_n_g_d_o_m, require drivers to buy some, but
not all, of these coverages. When a car is used as collateral for a loan the
lender usually requires specific coverage.
****** GGaapp iinnssuurraannccee[[_ee_dd_ii_tt_ _ss_oo_uu_rr_cc_eeÂÂ || _ee_dd_ii_tt]] ******
